@11:50 this scene is HILARIOUS!!!!!!! 
Thank you random lawyer, I'm certain you will increase your business 10 fold :)
Nintendo is one company that absolutely hates game streamers and gameplay uploads

@37:30 "...for folks who created 1 hit song...." It wouldn't have to suck for them: the burden of proof could 'simply' be reversed so-to-speak.
They could apply for "extended copyright".

As for who/what/when it could or should be granted....not trivial, but not impossible. Point being, it is NOT a valid argument against a 50 year limit as the 'default'.

@Tom_Scott The one large blemish on your otherwise solid video is 18:52 : 
"Or perhaps because they've seen the backlash that happens when horrible gamer children are suddenly denied something they *think* is their right... like our friend in the corner" 
Clearly you as a reactor is not a child and so both "horrible" and "gamer children" are meant as pejoratives. These pejoratives are not in keeping with the otherwise fact based spirit of this section. You notably never extend any pejoratives to large companies such as "these horrible greedy behemoths".
